\frac{1}{\pi}\int_0^\pi |\cos(x)|dx=\frac{1}{\pi}\int_0^{\pi/2} \cos(x)dx + \frac{1}{\pi}\int_{\pi/2}^{\pi} -\cos(x)dx=\frac{1}{\pi}[\sin(\pi/2)-\sin(0)-\sin(\pi)+\sin(\pi/2)]=\frac{1}{\pi}(1-0-0+1)=\frac{2}{\pi}
